text: Mozes Jacobs (26 November 1905 - 9 July 1943) was a Dutch gymnast. He competed in seven events at the 1928 Summer Olympics. He was killed in the Sobibor extermination camp during World War II. ==References== Category:1905 births Category:1943 deaths Category:Dutch male artistic gymnasts Category:Olympic gymnasts of the Netherlands Category:Gymnasts at the 1928 Summer Olympics Category:Dutch people who died in Sobibor extermination camp Category:Sportspeople from Amsterdam
